definitions.definition: Any of various carangid fish of genus Trachinotus or species Alectis ciliaris ( African pompano ), from coastal parts of the North Atlantic .
A Pacific pompano , an edible butterfish of species Peprilus simillimus .

main_definition: Any of various carangid fish of genus Trachinotus or species Alectis ciliaris ( African pompano ), from coastal parts of the North Atlantic . [from 16th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( chiefly US ) A Pacific pompano , an edible butterfish of species Peprilus simillimus . [from 19th c.]
